Kenya Railways Corporation said yesterday it will launch a train that will facilitate cross-county travel along the Standard Gauge Railway.The train service, expected to start operations in July, will make stops at Athi River, Emali, Kibwezi, Mtito, Voi, Miasenyi and Mariakani before the final stop at Miritini.&ldquo;Without a doubt, we have many passengers who intend to ply their businesses across the five counties that the line traverses and this new train will ensure that we play our role in devolution by connecting businesses across the counties,&rdquo; managing director Atanas Maina said in a statement yesterday.KRC has also partnered with the National Transport and Safety Authority to allow private bus operators to provide last mile services to and from the various destinations along the SGR route.